subSubSection.paragraph:
Head
.

— Brown to reddish-brown. Impunctate. Antennae entirely black and only the first basal antennomeres usually contrasting brown (
Fig. 45
). Ratio of length of second to third antennomere 0.75–1.00 (mean: 0.86); ratio of length of third to fourth antennomere 0.30–0.50 (mean: 0.39; 
Fig. 46
).
